MENINGITIS, MENINGOCOCCAL - NIGERIA
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Meningococcal vaccine need during Hajj 970304173207
Meningococcal vaccine need during Hajj (02) 970305164348
WHO communicable disease news, Mar. 12, 1996 960315
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 1998
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Agence France Presse, 11 Apr 1998

Two hundred and fifty cases of meningococcal meningitis have occurred in
Nigeria with 52 fatalities, 13 of which occurred the week of 5-11 April in
Gurin Village, northeastern part of the country.
Authorities said that the 200,000 doses of vaccine distributed in Adamawa
would cover only 20 percent of that state's population.
